#Text=spongework - a complex of irregular, interconnecting cavities intricately perforating the rock; the cavities may range from a few centimetres to more than a metre across.
#Text=spring - a natural flow of water from rock or soil onto the land surface or into a body of surface water.
#Text=stalactite - a speleothem hanging downwards from a roof or wall, of cylindrical or conical form, usually with a central hollow tube.
#Text=stalagmite - a speleothem projecting vertically upwards from a cave floor and formed by precipitation from drips.
#Text=steephead - a steep-sided valley in karst, generally short, ending abruptly upstream where a stream emerges or formerly did so.
#Text=straw - a long, thin-walled tubular stalactite less than about 1em in diameter.

#Text=subcutaneous zone - the uppermost layers of rock below the soil on a karst. this zone is distinguished from lower zones by a higher porosity and storage capacity for water as a result of the presence of many solutionally enlarged fissures.
#Text=subjacent karst - karst developed in soluble beds underlying other rock formations; the surface mayor may not be affected by the karst development.
#Text=sump - a point in a cave passage when the water meets the roof.
#Text=swirlhole - a hole in rock in a streambed eroded by eddying water, with or without sand or pebble tools.
#Text=syngenetic karst - karst developed in aeolian calcarenite when the evolution of karst features has taken place at the same time as the lithification of dune sand.
#Text=tafoni - roughly hemispherical hollows weathered in rock either at the surface or in caves.
#Text=through cave - a cave which may be followed from entrance to exit along a stream course or along a passage which formerly carried a stream.
#Text=tower karst - conekarst in which the residual hills have very steep to overhanging lower slopes. there my be alluvial plains between the towers and flat-floored depressions within them.
#Text=tracer - a material introduced into surface or underground water where it disappears or into soil to determine drainage interconnections and travel time.
